COMPONENT NAME: IKM MSSQL Slowly Changing Dimension COMPONENT VERSION: 10.1.3.2 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 10.1.3 and above
Description: - Integration Knowledge Module - Management of TYPE 2 Slowly Changing Dimensions on Microsoft SQLServer. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled.
To use this Knowledge Module: When defining the Target Datastore, it is necessary to set the following parameters (from the "Slowly Changing Dimensions Behavior" list box, on the "Description" tab of each column concerned): - Surrogate Key: A single column identifying Records. This column must be defined as an Identity column on the Target Data Server and should be: - Mapped to 0 (zero), - Executed on Target - Natural Key: Column(s) representing the Natural Key of the Record. - Overwrite Column: List of updatable column(s) (i.e. those that can be updated after modification of the original data). - Insert Row: List of column(s) representing the Slowly Changing Attributes (i.e. those that require a Record insert after modification of the original data) - Current Record Flag: A single numeric column mapped to 0 or 1 and representing the Current Record Flag status of the Record. It is automatically updated by the Knowledge Module (1 : Current Record ; 0 : Past Records) - Start Timestamp: A single date (or timestamp) column indicating the beginning of a Record's availability. The value is the current date (or timestamp). - End Timestamp: A single date (or timestamp) column indicating the end of the Record's availability. The value is a default of "01 January 2400"
Restrictions: - Make sure to map ALL target table columns flagged as: "Surrogate Key", "Natural Key", "Current Record Flag", "Start Timestamp" and "End Timestamp". Notice that mappings set for the "Current Record Flag", "Start Timestamp" and "End Timestamp" columns are not used. - As this Knowledge Module is dedicated to Datawarehouse Projects (where data should not be removed), when using it with a journalized Source Datastore, it is not possible to synchronize deletions. Therefore, data should be manually filtered to exclude any source delete events (add a filter on JRN_FLAG = 'I'). - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (i.e. with a Foreign Key). - Deletes are committed regardless of the COMMIT option. - The FLOW_CONTROL option calls the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data. If the Table Primary Key is designated by the same column as the Surrogate Key, then: 1. On the "Diagram" tab of the Interface, uncheck the "Check Not Null" checkbox for the column representing the Primary Key. 2. On the "Control" tab of the Interface and in the "Constraint" panel, set the option value to NO for the Primary Key control.
Commit all data inserted or updated in the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected from a previous control.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Check this option if you wish to analyze the target table before loading data into the integration table.

use <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_CATALOG")%>
create statistics <%=odiRef.getInfo("TARG_NAME")%>_stat on <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> (<%=odiRef.getColList("","[COL_NAME]",",\n\t\t","","")%>) with sample 10 percent

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> IND_UPDATE ) select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "convert([DEST_WRI_DT],'01-01-2400',110)", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> <%if (odiRef.getPop("HAS_JRN").equals("0")) {%> 'I' <%}else{%> JRN_FLAG <%}%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom()%> where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJoin()%> <%=odiRef.getFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=odiRef.getHaving()%>

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> IND_UPDATE ) select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> 'I' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> as E where not exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> as T where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= E.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> ) and E.ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>'

use <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_WORK_CATALOG")%>
create statistics <%=odiRef.getInfo("INT_NAME")%>_stat on <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> (<%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "")%>) with sample 10 percent

update S set IND_UPDATE = 'U' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> as T, <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> as S where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= S.[COL_NAME]", "
and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("and	", "T.[COL_NAME]	= 1", "
and	", "", "SCD_FLAG")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("and	", "((S.[COL_NAME] = T.[COL_NAME]) or ((S.[COL_NAME] is null) and (T.[COL_NAME] is null)))", "
and	", "", "(SCD_INS and !TRG)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("and	(", "((S.[COL_NAME] <> T.[COL_NAME]) and ((S.[COL_NAME] is not null) or (T.[COL_NAME] is not null))) ", "
 or	", ")", "(SCD_UPD and !TRG)")%>

Update S set S.IND_UPDATE = 'N' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> as T, <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> as S where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "S.[COL_NAME]	= T.[COL_NAME]", "
and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("and	", "T.[COL_NAME]	= 1", "
and	", "", "SCD_FLAG")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("and	", "((S.[COL_NAME] = T.[COL_NAME]) or ((S.[COL_NAME] is null) and (T.[COL_NAME] is null)))", "
and	", "", "((SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG)")%>

update T set <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = S.[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "T.[COL_NAME] = [EXPRESSION]", ",
	", "", "(((SCD_UPD) and TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> as T, <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> as S where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= S.[COL_NAME]", "
and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= 1", "
and	", "", "SCD_FLAG")%> and IND_UPDATE = 'U'

update T set <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = 0", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_FLAG and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = ", "", "", "(SCD_END and REW)")%><%=odiRef.getColList("", "S.[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> as T, <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> as S where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= S.[COL_NAME]", "
and	", "", "(SCD_NK)")%> and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= 1", "
and	", "", "(SCD_FLAG)")%> and S.IND_UPDATE = 'I'

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_FLAG and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> ) select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "1", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_FLAG AND REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> as S where S.IND_UPDATE = 'I'

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

use <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_CATALOG")%>
update statistics <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> (<%=odiRef.getInfo("TARG_NAME")%>_stat) with sample 10 percent
